OL,3,CWhy is the Middle East conflict
OL,4,Cpushing up energy prices in the UK?
OL,6,FResearch director at the security
OL,7,Fbrokerage company XTB, Kathleen Brooks
OL,8,Fsays Europe is "much less reliant on
OL,9,Fgas from Russia and the Middle East
OL,10,Fand instead gets the bulk of its LNG
OL,11,Ffrom the US", meaning markets could
OL,12,F"absorb a few weeks of disruption to
OL,13,FQatari LNG flow".
OL,15,FEssentially, experts think the longer-
OL,16,Fterm impact will largely depend on how
OL,17,Fquickly the conflict de-escalates or
OL,18,Fwhether it is likely to persist and
OL,19,Flead to prolonged disruption.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
